          <div class="msgRatings"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="msgContentFrame">I think you people have already planned some adjustments for this feature in the first major updates to hit the game later, which is great to hear, but I still want to explain how I think the playerbase may feel about the progression system in general.  <br /> <br />To use FFXI as an example, in that game you could gain Job Levels by acquiring EXP and Combat Skills by acquiring Skill Points.  <br /> <br />While in FFXIV you can gain Physical Levels by acquiring EXP and Class Ranks by acquiring Skill Points. <br /> <br />Looking at it from this point of view, the games have two fairly similar ways of making progress. There is the EXP points that are static and consistent, and there are Skill Points that are acquired randomly and erratically. <br /> <br />In FFXI, the focus of character development is on Job Levels, rather than Combat Skills. Combat Skills are not nearly as important, and it is generally assumed that if your Job Level is X, your primary Combat Skill is also X. It is clear that Job Levels are more important than Combat Skills in the way that players (and the game systems) perceive them. <br /> <br />Now in FFXIV, the focus of character development is on Class Ranks, rather than Physical Levels. Physical Levels are not nearly as important in the long run, as higher Class Rank allows you to equip better gear and stronger abilities and spells. You also only have to level Physical Level once. <br /> <br />Now <b>the problem</b> here is that while in FFXI the random and erratic Combat Skill up system was fine, much because players didn't think of it as important character development as Job Levels (in addition of being capped to your Job Level), in FFXIV the random and erratic Class Rank skill up system becomes more of a headache. <br /> <br />Why is this? It is because people want to see consistent rewards for their efforts, especially where it matters. Combat skills didn't matter in the long run as much as Job Levels did in FFXI, so the inconsistent rewards were more tolerable. It is not the case in FFXIV however, as Class Rank (and the random skill up system that comes with it) is seen as much more important feature than Physical Levels. Right now Physical Levels have the status of Combat Skills in XI, while the progression system is more like with the Job Level system.  <br /> <br />Now during the Beta you had changed the Class Rank system for Crafting and Gathering classes so that the rewards are more consistent, which is a big step up from XI in which due to random system you could have done 10 synthesis without gaining any skill up. I hope you can do the same for Combat. <br /> <br />The whole game feels like a one big &quot;Skill Up Party&quot; from XI at this point, which I am sure was not your original intention. People are also trying to lengthen their battles and fight only monsters with lots of HP, as it gives them more chances of gaining Skill. I don't think this is a good thing, to judge the monster based on his HP and not reward efficiency when trying to defeat it, but rather taking it slow. <br /> <br />I thank you for listening. Whatever you decide to do, try not to make it based on Random Number Generator :) Not every feature in the game needs it!<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>SE: <br /><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Quote:</div><div class="orig">We don't really want to compete against World of Warcraft or for example the new Star Wars MMO.</div></div> <br /></div></div>
